To: Trudy McEnearney <Trudy.McEnearney@Royalrehab.com.au>, Heath Maguire <heath@wolfiq.com.au>

Hi Heath,

Happy to leave the gallery as is for now, but could we re-visit this later so that they appear as full width hero images, but scroll through so that we still have the chance to show multiple shots?

We also have our 2022 course pages on the staging site ready for us to begin reviewing, but I don't think the look fits with our new design (this is carried over from current site)

https://staging-sargoodoncollaroy.kinsta.cloud/indoor-skydiving-2022/

Is there anything that can be done to our course pages to give them a bit of a freshening up, as we are due to share these with Sargood in the next week or so?

Is there also a new date on when the site will be ready to share with the resort manager?

Thanks Heath!

Britt

Kind regards,

Trudy.

Subject: Re: Sargood refreshed site - go live date

‌

Hi Britt,

Sorry I missed your email somehow.

The header images will be for each page. I would suggest to look at the current header galleries and select your favourite from the current ones and supply that in original resolution. This would need to be done for each page.

Hope that clears it up.

Personally though, I quite like the gallery format header as it exists. I feel it shows more of what Sargood has to offer (in a visual way). It seems a shame to remove all of the photos. Let me know what you think though? I would hate to change it for 'change sake' if that makes sense?

Thanks and speak soon,

‌

Heath Maguire
